http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/MCD-engineer-arrested/article13983053.ece

The Central Bureau of Investigation has arrested a Municipal Corporation of Delhi engineer on graft charges.Assistant Engineer Manish Goyal has been accused of demanding and accepting a bribe of Rs.30,000 for not demolishing a building.“A case under the Prevention of Corruption Act has been registered against the official on a complaint from the building owner,” said CBI spokesperson R.K. Gaur.The accused official had issued notices for the demolition of the complainant’s building and then demanded bribe to rescind the orders.“A CBI team laid a trap and arrested the engineer when he was accepting the bribe money. Searches are being conducted on his official and residential premises,” said Mr. Gaur.